  "prompt": "How Indian Air Force Chief SP Tyagi was involved in Augusta Westland Scam?",
  "response": "SP Tyagi, a former Chief of the Indian Air Force (IAF), was allegedly involved in the Augusta Westland VVIP helicopter procurement scam. Here are key details:\n\n1. Allegations:\n- He was accused of manipulating the tender specifications to favor Augusta Westland\n- Allegedly lowered the helicopter's operational ceiling from 6,000 meters to 4,500 meters\n- This modification allegedly helped Augusta Westland win the contract\n\n2. Bribery Charges:\n- Accused of receiving kickbacks through middlemen and relatives\n- Allegedly accepted bribes to influence the helicopter procurement process\n- Facilitated the purchase of 12 AgustaWestland helicopters for VIP transport\n\n3. Legal Proceedings:\n- Arrested by Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) in 2016\n- Charged with criminal conspiracy and corruption\n- Accused of violating provisions of Prevention of Corruption Act\n\n4. Consequences:\n- First former IAF Chief to be arrested in a corruption case\n- Case involved international investigations and diplomatic complications\n- Significant impact on India's defense procurement processes\n\nThe case highlighted systemic corruption in defense procurement and led to increased scrutiny of military equipment purchases.",
